{[%mdl 8256] A05: R騁i Opening: 1 Nf3 Nf6} 1. e4 d6 2. Nf3 Nf6 3. d3 g6 4. g3
Bg7 5. Bg2 O-O 6. O-O c5 7. Nbd2 Nc6 8. Qe2 (8. Nc4 h6 9. Bd2 e5 10. Re1 Be6
11. Ne3 d5 12. exd5 Nxd5 13. Nxd5 Bxd5 14. c4 Be6 15. Bc3 Qb6 16. Qe2 f6 17.
Nd2 Rfe8 18. Qe3 f5 {1/2-1/2 (18) Nikolac,J (2470)-Lalic,B (2600) Zadar 1997})
8... e5 9. c3 Re8 $146 (9... Ne8 10. Ne1 f5 11. f4 Nf6 12. Nc4 fxe4 13. dxe4
exf4 14. Bxf4 d5 15. exd5 Nxd5 16. Rd1 Nxf4 17. Rxf4 Qc7 18. Bd5+ Kh8 19. Rxf8+
Bxf8 20. Bxc6 bxc6 21. Qe5+ Qxe5 22. Nxe5 Be6 23. b3 a5 24. N1d3 {Ikeda,J 
(2275)-Smirnov,V (2392) Sydney 2010 1/2-1/2 (80)}) 10. h3 {Controls g4} d5 11.
Kh2 (11. exd5 Nxd5 12. Rd1 h6 $15) 11... dxe4 (11... d4 12. Rd1 $15) 12. dxe4 (
12. Nxe4 Nxe4 13. dxe4 b6 $11) 12... Be6 13. a4 Qc7 {Black has an active
position} 14. Ng5 Rad8 (14... Bd7 $142 $5 $15 {would keep Black in the game})
15. Nxe6 $14 {White forks: c5, c7+d8} Rxe6 {White has the pair of bishops} 16.
Nc4 Re7 17. f4 Nh5 18. f5 Red7 19. fxg6 hxg6 20. Bg5 f6 {Black threatens to
win material: f6xg5} 21. Be3 Bf8 (21... Rd3 $5 22. Rf3 Na5 23. Nxa5 Qxa5 24.
Bxc5 Rd2 25. Qc4+ Kh7 $16) 22. Bf3 Ng7 23. Bg4 Rf7 24. Bh6 Kh7 25. Bd2 (25. Bc1
Kg8 $16) 25... Ne7 (25... f5 $5 26. exf5 gxf5 27. Bxf5+ Rxf5 28. Rxf5 Nxf5 29.
Qh5+ Kg8 30. Qxf5 Qf7 31. Qg4+ Qg7 $18) 26. Rf2 f5 $2 (26... Nc8 $142 $16) 27.
Raf1 $18 f4 28. gxf4 exf4 29. Bxf4 $4 {releasing the pressure on the opponent.}
(29. Kg1 $142 {a pity that White didn't try this} g5 30. h4 $18) {[%tqu "En",
"","","","f7f4","",10]} 29... Rxf4 $14 {Mate threat} 30. Rxf4 (30. Rxf4 g5 {
Combination}) (30. Z0 $140 Rxf2+ {Mate threat}) 30... g5 31. e5 gxf4 32. Qe4+ {
White forks: f4} Kg8 (32... Ng6 33. Rxf4 Qc6 34. Bf3 $11) 33. Rxf4 (33. Qxf4
$142 Nc6 34. Bd1 Nxe5 35. Bb3 (35. Qxe5 $2 Qxe5+ 36. Nxe5 Bd6 $19) 35... Nxc4
36. Bxc4+ Kh7 37. Qxc7 Bd6+ 38. Qxd6 Rxd6 39. Kg3 $18) 33... Re8 $4 {forfeits
the clear win} (33... Qc6 $142 $5 $11 {would keep Black alive}) 34. Be2 (34.
Nd6 $142 {secures the win} Qc6 35. Qxc6 Nxc6 36. Nxe8 Nxe8 37. Be6+ Kg7 38.
Rf7+ Kg8 39. Rxb7+ Kh8 40. Bd7 Nxe5 41. Bxe8 $18) 34... Qc6 (34... Ngf5 $142
35. Bh5 Rd8 36. Rxf5 Nxf5 37. Qxf5 Qg7 $16) 35. Qe3 $4 {ignoring the path to
victory} (35. Nd6 $142 {would have given White a clear advantage} Qxe4 36. Rxe4
$18) 35... Nd5 $19 36. Rxf8+ $4 {White has lost his nerve... understandable
when you consider his position} (36. Bf3 $142 Nxe3 37. Bxc6 bxc6 38. Nxe3 Rxe5
39. Nc4 Re2+ 40. Kg1 $19) 36... Rxf8 37. Qg3 Nf4 38. Bf3 (38. Bf1 {a fruitless
try to alter the course of the game} Kh8 $19) 38... Qxa4 39. Bd5+ (39. Ne3 {
desperation} Qb5 40. Qf2 $19) 39... Nxd5 (39... Nxd5 40. Qd3 Rf2+ 41. Kg3 Rg2+
42. Kf3 Qd7 43. Qd1 Qxh3+ 44. Ke4 Nb6 45. Qf3 Qh7+ 46. Ke3 Nxc4+ 47. Kf4 Ne6#)
0-1

