{[%mdl 8192] A29: English Opening: Four Knights Variation with 4 g3} 1. c4 e5
2. Nc3 Nf6 3. Nf3 Nc6 4. g3 d6 5. Bg2 Be7 6. O-O O-O 7. d3 h6 (7... Be6 8. Ng5
Nd7 9. Nxe6 fxe6 10. Rb1 Rb8 11. b4 Nd4 12. e3 Nf5 13. Ne2 Bf6 14. d4 exd4 15.
e4 Ne7 16. Nxd4 Bxd4 17. Qxd4 Nc6 18. Qc3 Qf6 19. Qxf6 Rxf6 20. f4 e5 21. Be3
a5 22. Bh3 {Von Herman,U (2416)-Kevorkov,A (2277) Germany 2013 1-0 (45)}) 8.
Rb1 Rb8 $146 (8... Be6 9. Nd2 (9. b4 a6 10. a4 e4 11. dxe4 Bxc4 12. b5 Na5 13.
Nd4 Re8 14. Nf5 Bf8 15. Be3 Be6 16. Nd4 Bc8 17. Qd3 Ng4 18. Bc1 Ne5 19. Qc2
Nac4 20. f4 Nd7 21. Nd5 Ndb6 22. Nxb6 Nxb6 23. Bd2 axb5 {Balduan,M (2289)
-Kujovic,M (2406) Germany 2003 1/2-1/2}) 9... a5 10. Nd5 Nd7 11. Ne4 f5 12.
Nec3 Nc5 13. Be3 Bd7 14. Nxe7+ Qxe7 15. Nd5 Qd8 16. d4 Ne6 17. dxe5 dxe5 18.
Bd2 Be8 19. e3 Qg5 20. f4 Qh5 21. Bc3 Qxd1 22. Rbxd1 Bh5 23. Rd2 {Spulber,C 
(2326)-Posedaru,B (2190) Eforie Nord 2007 1-0 (49)}) (8... a5 9. a3 Be6 10. b4
axb4 11. axb4 e4 12. dxe4 Bxc4 13. b5 Na5 14. Nd4 Nd7 15. Nd5 Bxd5 16. exd5 Bf6
17. Nf5 Nc5 18. Qc2 b6 19. Rb4 Nab7 20. Rg4 Kh8 21. Bb2 Rg8 22. h4 Ra2 23. Bxf6
{Charon Mustelier,M (2167)-Espinosa Escala,R (2251) Havana 2011 1/2-1/2 (33)})
9. b4 a6 {Consolidates b5} 10. a4 Qe8 (10... Be6 11. b5 Nd4 12. Nxd4 exd4 13.
Nd5 Nxd5 14. cxd5 $14) 11. b5 $14 axb5 12. axb5 Nd8 13. b6 (13. Ra1 Ne6 $16)
13... c6 {Prevents intrusion on b5+d5} 14. Qa4 Ne6 15. Qa7 {White threatens to
win material: Qa7xb8} (15. Ra1 Nc5 16. Qb4 e4 17. dxe4 Nfxe4 18. Nxe4 Nxe4 $14)
15... Bd7 $11 16. Qa2 Qc8 (16... Ra8 17. Qb2 $15) 17. Bd2 (17. Qb2 Ra8 $14)
17... Ra8 {Black threatens to win material: Ra8xa2} 18. Qb2 Qb8 19. Ra1 Nc5 20.
Rxa8 Qxa8 21. Ra1 {White threatens to win material: Ra1xa8} Na6 (21... Qb8 22.
Na4 Ne6 23. Nh4 $14) 22. e4 (22. d4 Qb8 $14) 22... Qb8 23. d4 exd4 24. Nxd4 Re8
25. Nd1 (25. e5 $5 dxe5 26. Nxc6 Bxc6 27. Bxc6 $14) 25... Bf8 26. f3 {Covers g4
} Qc8 (26... d5 $5 {should be considered} 27. exd5 cxd5 $11) 27. Ne3 Kh7 (27...
Nc5 28. Nb3 d5 29. cxd5 cxd5 30. exd5 (30. Nxd5 Nxd5 31. Nc1 Na4 32. Rxa4 Bxa4
33. exd5 Qc5+ 34. Kh1 Qf2 $19) 30... Nxb3 31. Qxb3 $11) 28. Bc3 Nh5 29. Rd1 g6
{Secures f5} (29... Nc5 30. Qa3 $14) 30. Ne2 (30. Nb3 Be7 $16) 30... Be6 {
Black has a cramped position} 31. g4 {White threatens to win material: g4xh5}
Ng7 32. Nf4 Nc5 33. Qb1 (33. Be1 h5 34. h3 Qd8 $11) 33... Nd7 (33... Bd7 34.
Bf6 $11) 34. h4 {Black has a cramped position} (34. Bd4 Ne5 $14) 34... Ne5 (
34... Qd8 35. Nfd5 cxd5 36. cxd5 Qxh4 37. dxe6 Nxe6 38. Qb5 $11) 35. h5 {
White gets more space} (35. Qc2 Kg8 $16) 35... g5 {Black threatens to win
material: g5xf4} 36. Ne2 (36. Nxe6 $5 {should be examined more closely} Nxe6
37. Qc2 $14) 36... Nxc4 $15 37. e5+ $2 (37. Nxc4 $142 $5 {and White is still
in the game} Bxc4 38. Ng3 $15) 37... Kg8 $17 38. Nxc4 Bxc4 39. Ng3 dxe5 40. Ne4
(40. Kh1 Bd5 41. Re1 Qb8 $19) 40... Qe6 41. Rd7 Rb8 42. Qa1 (42. Qb2 $142 Bd5
43. Nf6+ Qxf6 44. Bxe5 $19) 42... Ba6 $4 {Black loses the upper hand} (42...
Bd5 $142 {would have given Black the upper hand} 43. Nf6+ Qxf6 44. Bxe5 Qe6 45.
Rxd5 cxd5 (45... Qxd5 $6 46. Bxb8 Qc5+ 47. Kh2 $19) 46. Bxb8 Qxb6+ 47. Kh1 Ne6
$19) 43. Bxe5 $11 Re8 $4 {gives the opponent counterplay} (43... Ne8 44. Rxb7
Rxb7 45. Qxa6 Qxe5 46. Qxb7 Nf6 47. Qxc6 Nxe4 48. Qxe4 Bc5+ 49. Kf1 Qb2 $17)
44. Nf6+ $18 Kh8 45. Qb1 (45. Bc3 $142 {secures victory} Be7 46. Nxe8 Qxd7 47.
Bxg7+ (47. Nxg7 $143 Kh7 $18) 47... Kg8 48. Bxh6 Bc5+ 49. Kh2 $18) 45... Nf5
46. Qxf5 $4 {allows the opponent back into the game} (46. f4 $142 {and White
gets the upper hand} gxf4 47. Qe4 (47. gxf5 {is the less attractive alternative
} Qxe5 48. Rxf7 Bg7 49. Rxg7 Kxg7 (49... Qxf6 $6 50. Rg6 Qc3 51. Kh2 $11) 50.
Nxe8+ Qxe8 $17) 47... Qxe5 48. Rxf7 $18 (48. Nxe8 $6 {is clearly weaker} Qc5+
49. Kh2 Qf2 50. Qxf5 Qg3+ 51. Kh1 Qe1+ 52. Kh2 Qg3+ 53. Kh1 Qe1+ 54. Kh2 Qg3+
$11)) 46... Qxf5 $15 47. gxf5 Rxe5 48. Ng4 $4 {A valuable piece} (48. Bf1 Bxf1
49. Kxf1 Rxf5 $15) 48... Re1+ $4 {overlooking an easy win} (48... Rxf5 $142 {
nails it down} 49. Bf1 Bc5+ 50. Kg2 Rd5 51. Rxd5 Bxf1+ (51... cxd5 $143 52.
Bxa6 bxa6 53. b7 $16) 52. Kxf1 cxd5 53. Nxh6 Kg7 54. Nf5+ Kf6 $19) 49. Kf2 $11
{White threatens to win material: Kf2xe1} Re2+ 50. Kg3 Kg8 $4 (50... Re8 51.
Nf6 Re7 52. Rd8 $11) 51. Nf6+ (51. Rd8 $142 {and White wins} f6 52. Bf1 $18)
51... Kg7 $14 {Black threatens to win material: Kg7xf6} 52. Ne4 Rb2 $2 (52...
Re3 $142 {and Black could well hope to play on} 53. f6+ Kg8 $14) 53. f6+ $18
Kg8 54. Bh3 $4 {hands over the advantage to the opponent} (54. Rd8 $142 {
White would have gained the upper hand} c5 55. Nxc5 $18) 54... Rxb6 $11 55. Nd6
$2 (55. Rd8 $142 {and White is still in the game} c5 56. Nxc5 $11) 55... c5 $19
56. Ne8 $4 {White crumbles in face of a dire situation} (56. Ne4 Rc6 57. Rd8
$19) 56... Rc6 (56... c4 {might be the shorter path} 57. Nc7 Rxf6 58. Nxa6 $19)
57. Bf5 (57. Rd8 $19) 57... b5 (57... c4 $142 $19 {and the result of the game
is clear: Black will win}) 58. Be4 $14 {White threatens to win material: Be4xc6
} Rc8 $4 (58... Re6 59. Bd5 Bc8 60. Bxe6 Bxd7 61. Bxd7 $18) 59. Nd6 (59. Bd5
$142 {and White has prevailed} Kh8 60. Bxf7 $18) 59... Bxd6+ $4 (59... b4 $142
{and Black has air to breath} 60. Nxf7 Bb5 61. Nxh6+ Bxh6 $11) 60. Rxd6 $18 c4
$2 (60... b4 $142 61. Rxa6 Rb8 $18) 61. Rxa6 c3 (61... b4 62. Rb6 b3 63. Bf5
$18) 62. Bc2 b4 (62... Kf8 {is the last straw} 63. Bf5 Rb8 $18) 63. Rb6 Kf8 64.
Rxb4 Ke8 65. Rd4 Rc5 (65... Rb8 {does not win a prize} 66. Ba4+ Kf8 67. Bb3 $18
) 66. Kf2 (66. Ba4+ Rc6 67. Bxc6+ Kf8 68. Rd8#) 66... Rc6 (66... Rc8 $18 {
there is nothing else anyway}) 67. Ba4 (67. Ba4 c2 68. Bxc6+ Kf8 69. Rd8#) 1-0

