{[%mdl 8192] B33: Sicilian: Pelikan and Sveshnikov Variations} 1. e4 c5 2. Nf3
Nc6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 e5 6. Nf3 Bb4 7. Bd3 Bxc3+ 8. bxc3 d5 $146 (
8... O-O 9. Bg5 h6 10. Bh4 Qa5 11. Bxf6 Qxc3+ 12. Nd2 gxf6 13. O-O Kh7 14. f4
d6 15. f5 Rg8 16. Bc4 Rg7 17. Rb1 Nd4 18. Bd3 b6 19. Nc4 d5 20. Nd6 Qc5 21. Ne8
Rg5 22. Nxf6+ Kh8 23. Kh1 {Bense,J (2220)-Marosi,C (2295) Kecskemet 1990 1-0 
(39)}) 9. Qe2 (9. exd5 Qxd5 10. O-O O-O $11) 9... h6 {Controls g5} (9... dxe4
10. Bxe4 Nxe4 11. Qxe4 $17) 10. Nd2 (10. O-O O-O $11) 10... d4 {Black
threatens to win material: d4xc3} (10... O-O 11. O-O $15) 11. Bb2 $11 Qa5 $4 {
throwing away the advantage} (11... O-O $142 $5 $11 {is worth consideration})
12. Nb3 (12. Nc4 $5 Qa4 13. cxd4 Nxd4 14. Bxd4 exd4 15. O-O $16) 12... Qb6 13.
Bb5 (13. cxd4 Nxd4 14. Bxd4 exd4 $16) 13... Nxe4 (13... dxc3 $5 {should not be
overlooked} 14. Bxc3 O-O $11) 14. cxd4 $14 O-O 15. Bd3 (15. Bxc6 $142 $5 {
is the best option White has} Qxc6 16. dxe5 $14) 15... Qb4+ $15 16. c3 $2 (16.
Kf1 $142 {would keep White in the game} Nc3 17. a3 Qxb3 18. cxb3 Nxe2 19. Kxe2
Nxd4+ 20. Bxd4 exd4 21. Rhe1 $15) 16... Nxc3 $19 17. Qd2 (17. Bxc3 Qxc3+ 18.
Qd2 Qxd2+ 19. Kxd2 Rd8 $19) 17... exd4 18. Nxd4 Re8+ (18... Nxd4 $6 19. Bxc3
Qe7+ 20. Qe3 Qxe3+ 21. fxe3 $17) 19. Kf1 Nxa2 (19... Qxd4 $6 20. Qxc3 Rd8 21.
Be4 $17) (19... Nxd4 {is the weaker alternative} 20. Bxc3 Qa4 21. Bxd4 $11) 20.
Qxb4 Naxb4 ({Worse is} 20... Ncxb4 21. Bc4 $14) 21. Bb5 Bd7 22. Ba3 (22. Nxc6
Bxc6 23. Bxc6 Nxc6 $19) 22... Nd5 (22... Rad8 $142 $5 {seems even better} 23.
Bxc6 Nxc6 24. Nxc6 Bxc6 25. h4 $19) 23. Nxc6 Bxc6 (23... Nc3 24. Ba4 bxc6 25.
Bd1 $19) 24. Bxc6 bxc6 25. g3 Re4 26. Bc5 (26. Kg2 $142 $19) 26... Nc7 $4 {
letting the wind out of his own sails} (26... a5 $142 $19 {Black had this
great chance}) 27. Rxa7 $17 Rxa7 28. Bxa7 Rc4 29. Ke2 c5 30. Ra1 Kf8 (30...
Rc2+ 31. Ke3 $17) 31. Ra5 $15 {[%cal Ra5c5,Ra7c5,Gc4c5] The isolani on c5
becomes a target} Ne6 32. Kd3 Rc1 33. Kd2 Rh1 34. h4 Nd4 $4 {Black has let it
slip away. The knight dominates} (34... Rf1 35. Ke2 Rc1 36. Kd2 $11) 35. Kd3 (
35. Bxc5+ $142 {and White takes home the point} Kg8 36. Bxd4 $18) 35... Rd1+
$11 36. Kc4 {White threatens to win material: Kc4xc5} Rc1+ 37. Kd5 {[%cal
Ra5c5,Ra7c5,Rd5c5,Gc1c5] Increasing the pressure on the isolated pawn on c5}
Nb3 {Black threatens to win material: Nb3xa5} 38. Rb5 c4 39. Be3 Rc2 40. Rb4 {
[%cal Rb4c4,Rd5c4,Gc2c4] Attacking the isolated pawn on c4} Nd2 41. Bc5+ (41.
Rb8+ Ke7 $11) 41... Kg8 42. Rb8+ Kh7 43. Rb7 Kg6 44. Rb6+ Kf5 (44... f6 45. Be3
$15) 45. Bd4 {White threatens to win material: Bd4xg7} (45. Rb7 Kg6 $11) 45...
Ne4 (45... f6 46. Rb7 $15) 46. Bxg7 $11 c3 $4 {with this move Black loses his
initiative} (46... Rxf2 $142 47. g4+ Kxg4 48. Kxe4 Kxh4 49. Rxh6+ Kg4 $11) 47.
Bxh6 $4 {weakening the position} (47. f3 $142 {White has the better game} Rd2+
48. Bd4 $18) 47... Rb2 {Black threatens to win material: Rb2xb6} (47... Rd2+
$142 48. Kc6 Rxf2 49. Rb5+ Kg4 $19) 48. Rc6 $11 Nxf2 (48... Rd2+ $5 {is
noteworthy} 49. Kc4 Rxf2 $11) 49. Rxc3 $14 Rd2+ $4 (49... Re2 $142 $14 {
was a good chance to save the game}) 50. Bxd2 $18 (50. Bxd2 Kg4 51. Rc7 $18)
1-0

