e5 Rg8 {Allen,D (2250)-Ma,E (2200) Istanbul 2000 1/2-1/2 (41)}) 8... d6 9. h3 {
Secures g4} a6 {Prevents intrusion on b5} 10. Be3 b5 (10... c5 11. Nf3 $14) 11.
a3 {Black has a cramped position} (11. f4 $5 Nc4 12. Bxc4 bxc4 13. Nc6 $16)
11... Bb7 12. f3 {Covers g4} c5 (12... g6 13. Qd2 $11) 13. Nf5 $14 c4 {Black
threatens to win material: c4xb3} 14. Ba2 Qd7 (14... Bc8 15. Nxe7+ Qxe7 16. Qd2
$14) 15. Nxe7+ (15. Qd2 $5 $16) 15... Qxe7 $14 16. b3 (16. Qd2 h6 $14) 16...
Rac8 17. bxc4 (17. Qd2 $142 $5 $14 {has some apparent merit}) 17... Nxc4 $15
18. Bxc4 Rxc4 {Praise the rook!} 19. Ne2 (19. Qd3 Qc7 20. Bd4 Nd7 $15) 19... d5
20. Ng3 $2 (20. e5 $142 $17) 20... dxe4 $19 21. fxe4 Nxe4 (21... Bxe4 $142 $5
22. Nxe4 Nxe4 $19) 22. Nf5 $17 Qe5 (22... Qe8 23. Bh6 Ng3 (23... gxh6 $143 24.
Qg4+ Ng5 25. Nxh6+ Kh8 26. Qxg5 $16) 24. Nxg3 Qc6 $17) 23. Qg4 $4 {there were
better ways to keep up the pressure} (23. Bd4 Qe6 24. Qg4 g5 $11) 23... g6 $4 {
gives the opponent counterplay} (23... Bc8 $142 {and Black could have gained
the advantage} 24. Rae1 Bxf5 (24... Rxc2 $4 {a poisoned pawn} 25. Nh6+ Kh8 26.
Nxf7+ Rxf7 27. Rxf7 $18) 25. Qxf5 Qxf5 26. Rxf5 Re8 $19) 24. Nh6+ $11 Kg7 25.
Nf5+ $4 {White is ruining his position} (25. Nxf7 $142 {would save the game}
Rxf7 26. Rxf7+ Kxf7 27. Qd7+ Kg8 28. Qd8+ Kg7 29. Qd7+ Kg8 30. Qd8+ Kf7 31.
Qd7+ Kg8 $11) 25... Kh8 $19 26. Bh6 (26. Nh6 f5 27. Qd1 $19) 26... Rg8 (26...
gxf5 $142 {seems even better} 27. Qf4 Qc5+ 28. Qe3 $19) 27. Bg7+ $4 {causes
even greater problems} (27. Ne3 Rc6 28. Qd7 $11) 27... Rxg7 $19 28. Nxg7 (28.
Ne3 {does not improve anything} Qc5 29. Rae1 Rxc2 $19) 28... Kxg7 (28... Ng3
$142 {and Black has prevailed} 29. Qd7 Ne2+ 30. Kh1 $19) 29. Qd7 (29. Qf3 {
desperation} Bd5 30. Qe3 $19) 29... Bd5 30. Rad1 Be6 (30... Nc3 {might be the
shorter path} 31. Rd2 Rd4 32. Rxd4 Ne2+ 33. Kf2 Qxd4+ 34. Ke1 $19) 31. Qb7 (31.
Qe7 {the only chance to get some counterplay} Ng5 32. Rd3 Rxc2 33. Qd6 $19)
31... Qc5+ (31... Rxc2 $142 {and Black can celebrate victory} 32. Qa7 Nc5 33.
Qa8 Qe3+ 34. Kh1 $19) 32. Kh2 Qxa3 (32... Ng5 $142 {and Black can already relax
} 33. c3 Rxc3 34. Qb8 $19) 33. Rd3 (33. Qa7 {hardly improves anything} Qb2 34.
c3 Qxc3 $19) 33... Qb2 34. Rdf3 (34. Qa7 {doesn't improve anything} Rxc2 35.
Qd4+ Qxd4 36. Rxd4 Nc3 $19) 34... Qe5+ (34... Qxc2 $6 {is a useless try} 35.
Rxf7+ Bxf7 36. Qxf7+ Kh6 37. Qf8+ Kh5 38. Qf3+ Kg5 39. Qe3+ Kh5 40. Qf3+ Kg5
41. Qe3+ Kh5 42. Qf3+ $11) 35. Kg1 Ng5 36. Rd3 (36. R3f2 {does not win a prize}
Bd5 37. Qd7 Rh4 $19) 36... Rxc2 37. Rd8 Nxh3+ $1 {Deflection: g2} 38. Kh1 (38.
gxh3 Qh2# {Mate attack Deflection Pinning}) 38... Nf4 (38... Qh5 39. Rxf7+ Bxf7
40. Qe4 Nf2+ 41. Kg1 Qh1#) 39. Qe7 Qh5+ (39... Qh5+ 40. Qh4 Qxh4+ 41. Kg1 Rxg2#
) 0-1

