10. bxc3 Qxb5 11. dxc6 Nxc6 12. Qd6 f6 13. Ba3 Kf7 14. Rab1 Qa6 15. Nd4 Re8 16.
Nb5 Na5 17. Qxa6 bxa6 18. Nd6+ {1-0 (18) Westerinen,H (2335)-Andersson,B (2277)
Fredericia 2013}) 5... Nge7 6. c3 {Consolidates b4+d4} a6 {Black threatens to
win material: a6xb5} 7. Bf1 (7. Bxc6 Nxc6 8. d4 cxd4 9. cxd4 Bg7 $14) 7... d5 (
7... Bg7 8. d4 cxd4 9. cxd4 $11) 8. d4 (8. exd5 Qxd5 9. d4 cxd4 10. cxd4 Bg7
$14) 8... c4 {Black gains space} (8... dxe4 $5 9. Rxe4 Bg7 $15) 9. Bg5 (9. exd5
exd5 10. Nbd2 Bh6 $16) 9... Bg7 $14 10. Nbd2 O-O 11. b3 {White threatens to
win material: b3xc4} f6 {Black threatens to win material: f6xg5} 12. Bh4 b5 (
12... g5 13. exd5 Nxd5 14. bxc4 Nxc3 $11) 13. a4 (13. bxc4 bxc4 14. Rb1 Ra7 $14
) 13... Bd7 (13... b4 14. exd5 Nxd5 15. Nxc4 $17) 14. Bg3 (14. bxc4 $142 bxc4
15. Bg3 $14) 14... e5 $2 (14... b4 $142 {and Black is still in the game} 15.
exd5 Nxd5 16. bxc4 Nxc3 $14) 15. axb5 axb5 16. Rxa8 Qxa8 17. bxc4 dxc4 18. d5 {
White threatens to win material: d5xc6} (18. dxe5 $5 Qa7 19. exf6 Bxf6 20. e5
$16) 18... Nd8 $14 19. Nxc4 (19. Qb1 $142 $5 $14 {is a viable option}) 19...
bxc4 $17 20. Bxc4 (20. Nd2 Nc8 $17) 20... Kh8 (20... Nc8 $5 $19) 21. Qb3 Nb7
22. h3 (22. Qb4 Nc8 $17) 22... Nd6 23. Nd2 (23. Bd3 Rb8 24. Qc2 Qa3 $19) 23...
Rb8 (23... Bh6 24. Nf3 Rb8 25. Qa2 Qxa2 26. Bxa2 $19) 24. Qd1 (24. Qc2 Qa3 25.
Rb1 Rxb1+ 26. Qxb1 Nec8 $19 (26... Nxc4 27. Nxc4 Qxc3 28. Qb8+ Ng8 29. Nb6 $15)
) 24... Bh6 25. Bd3 Rb2 (25... Qa3 26. Nb1 Qa1 27. c4 $19) 26. Nc4 Nxc4 27.
Bxc4 Nc8 28. d6 $2 (28. Re2 $142 Rxe2 29. Bxe2 $17) 28... Rd2 (28... Nb6 {
and Black can already relax} 29. Bd5 Qa3 30. Qf3 Qxd6 31. c4 $19) 29. Qb3 Nxd6
(29... Bc6 {might be the shorter path} 30. d7 Rxd7 31. Be6 $19) 30. Bd5 Bc6 31.
c4 Bxd5 32. cxd5 (32. exd5 Qa7 $19) 32... Qa7 33. Qb4 Nf7 (33... Qc7 34. Ra1
$19) 34. Qc3 $2 (34. Rc1 $142 Kg7 35. Rc8 Rd1+ 36. Kh2 $19) 34... Bf4 (34...
Ra2 {seems even better} 35. Kh1 Kg7 36. Rd1 $19) 35. Rf1 Bh6 36. Qc6 $4 {
throwing away the advantage} (36. Re1 Ra2 37. Qf3 $19) 36... Qe7 (36... Kg7
$142 $5 {makes it even easier for Black} 37. Qc4 $19) 37. Ra1 Bf8 38. Bh4 g5
39. Bg3 h5 (39... Kg7 $142 40. Kh2 h5 $19) 40. Qa8 $4 {shortens the misery for
White} (40. h4 Kg8 $19) 40... Qc5 (40... h4 $142 {and Black has reached his
goal} 41. Qa5 Rd4 $19) 41. h4 Rc2 (41... Kg7 42. Qb7 Qb4 43. Qxb4 Bxb4 44. f3
$19) 42. Ra5 (42. hxg5 $5 Nxg5 43. Ra6 $17) 42... Qc8 $19 43. Qa7 $4 {an
oversight. But White was lost anyway.} (43. Qxc8 Rxc8 44. Ra2 Rc1+ 45. Kh2 Bc5
$19) 43... Rc7 (43... Kg7 $142 {keeps an even firmer grip} 44. Ra1 gxh4 45.
Bxh4 $19) 44. Qb6 (44. Qa6 Kg7 45. Kh2 Qxa6 46. Rxa6 Rc2 $19) 44... Bd6 45.
hxg5 $2 (45. Kh2 $19) 45... fxg5 46. Qb3 (46. Ra7 {does not help much} Rxa7 47.
Qxa7 Kg7 $19) 46... Rc1+ 47. Kh2 h4 48. Qf3 (48. Bxh4 {doesn't get the cat off
the tree} Kg7 49. Qh3 Qxh3+ 50. Kxh3 Rh1+ 51. Kg4 Rxh4+ 52. Kf3 Rf4+ 53. Ke3 g4
$19) 48... hxg3+ 49. fxg3 (49. Qxg3 {is still a small chance} Re1 50. Qh3+
Qxh3+ 51. gxh3 Rxe4 52. Kg2 $19) 49... Kg7 50. Ra7 (50. g4 {does not save the
day} Bc5 51. d6 Qh8+ 52. Qh3 Bg1+ 53. Kh1 Be3+ 54. Kh2 Bf4+ 55. g3 Rh1+ 56.
Kxh1 Qxh3+ 57. Kg1 Be3#) 50... Qh8+ 51. Qh5 Qxh5# 0-1

