{[%mdl 8192] E97: King's Indian: Classical Main Line (6...e5 7 0-0 Nc6): 8 Be3
and 8 d5 Ne7, not 9 Ne1} 1. c4 Nf6 2. Nc3 d6 3. d4 g6 4. e4 Bg7 5. Nf3 O-O 6.
Be2 e5 7. O-O Nc6 8. d5 Ne7 9. h3 Nd7 (9... Ne8 10. Bg5 f6 11. Bh4 Kh8 12. Qd2
Ng8 13. b4 Qe7 14. Rab1 h5 15. Bg3 Bh6 16. Qd3 Ng7 17. Bh4 g5 18. Bg3 f5 19. c5
f4 20. Bh2 g4 21. hxg4 hxg4 22. Nd2 Nh5 23. cxd6 cxd6 24. g3 {WoDra (2534)
-McShane (2381) playchess.com INT 2006 0-1 (35)}) (9... a5 10. Be3 Ne8 11. Qd2
f5 12. exf5 gxf5 13. Bh6 f4 14. Bxg7 Nxg7 15. Bd3 Nef5 16. Rfe1 Nh5 17. a3 Bd7
18. b4 Qe7 19. Nb5 Be8 20. Bxf5 Rxf5 21. bxa5 Qg7 22. Kh1 Nf6 23. Rg1 Rh5 24.
Kh2 {Da Silva,H (2219)-Violla Cunha,M (2322) Rio de Janeiro 2015 0-1 (31)}) 10.
Be3 a6 $146 {Covers b5} (10... f5 11. exf5 gxf5 12. Ng5 Nf6 13. f4 Bh6 14. Qd2
exf4 15. Bxf4 Ng6 16. g3 Nxf4 17. gxf4 Ne4 18. Ncxe4 fxe4 19. Qe3 Qf6 20. Bg4
Bxg4 21. hxg4 Bxg5 22. fxg5 Qxb2 23. Qxe4 Rae8 24. Rxf8+ Rxf8 25. Rf1 {Grachev,
B (2483)-Gubajdullin,A (2344) Samara 2003 1/2-1/2 (41)}) (10... a5 11. Qa4 $14)
11. a4 (11. a3 f5 $14) 11... f5 $14 {Nimzovich: attack the chain at its base}
12. Ng5 Nf6 13. f4 (13. Qb3 h6 14. Ne6 Bxe6 15. dxe6 fxe4 $14) 13... Nxe4 14.
Ngxe4 fxe4 15. Nxe4 (15. g4 $5 $11 {looks like a viable alternative}) 15... Nf5
$17 16. Bc1 exf4 17. Rxf4 Bh6 {Black threatens to win material: Bh6xf4} (17...
Qe7 $142 $5 18. Bd3 Bd7 $17) 18. Rf3 Bxc1 19. Rxc1 {Black has a cramped
position} Qe7 20. Qd3 Bd7 21. b3 {Consolidates a4} (21. Re1 Bxa4 22. g4 Rae8
$17) 21... Rae8 $17 22. Nc3 Qg5 {Black threatens to win material: Qg5xc1} (
22... Ne3 $142 $5 23. Rxf8+ Rxf8 $17) 23. Rcf1 $15 Ne3 (23... Nh4 24. Rxf8+
Rxf8 25. Rxf8+ Kxf8 26. g4 $11) 24. Rxf8+ $11 Rxf8 25. Rxf8+ Kxf8 {Black has a
mate threat} 26. Bf3 Bxh3 {[%cal Re3g2,Rg5g2,Rh3g2,Gf3g2,Gg1g2] Will g2 fall?}
27. Qd2 Bd7 $4 {with this move Black loses his initiative} (27... Qf4 28. Ne2
Qg5 29. Nc3 $11) 28. Ne4 $4 {ruins a clearly superior position} (28. Nd1 $142
$18 {White has a promising position}) 28... Qf4 $15 29. g3 $4 (29. c5 h5 $11)
29... Qh6 (29... Qxf3 $142 {and Black has triumphed} 30. Qf2 Qxf2+ 31. Kxf2 Nc2
$19) 30. Nf6 {White threatens to win material: Nf6xd7} Bh3 31. g4 $2 (31. c5
Ng4 (31... dxc5 $143 32. d6 cxd6 33. Qxd6+ Kf7 34. Ne4 $16) 32. Qxh6+ Nxh6 33.
cxd6 cxd6 34. Nxh7+ Kg7 $15) 31... Kg7 $4 {Black threatens to win material:
Kg7xf6. forfeits the advantage} (31... Qf4 32. Qf2 Kg7 33. Ne8+ Kf7 34. Nxc7
Nxg4 35. Bxg4 Qxf2+ 36. Kxf2 Bxg4 37. b4 $19) 32. Ne8+ $4 {allows the opponent
back into the game} (32. Qd4 $142 {would be a reprieve} Kf7 33. Qe4 Kxf6 34.
Qe6+ Kg7 35. Qd7+ Kg8 36. Qe6+ Kf8 37. Qc8+ Ke7 38. Qe6+ Kd8 39. Qg8+ Kd7 40.
Qe6+ Kd8 41. Qg8+ Kd7 42. Qe6+ Kd8 $11) 32... Kf7 $19 33. Nxc7 Qf4 34. Qf2 Nxg4
35. Bxg4 Qxf2+ 36. Kxf2 Bxg4 37. b4 h5 38. c5 Ke7 (38... dxc5 $142 $5 39. bxc5
Bd7 $19) 39. c6 $17 bxc6 (39... Kd8 40. Ne6+ Kc8 41. cxb7+ Kxb7 42. a5 $17) 40.
dxc6 {White has a new passed pawn: c6. Black has a new passed pawn: d6} Kd8 41.
Nxa6 Bd1 42. c7+ $4 (42. a5 $142 {this is the best way to fight back} Ba4 43.
Nb8 $15) 42... Kc8 $19 43. b5 Bxa4 44. b6 Bd7 45. Nb4 (45. Nb8 Bh3 46. Nc6 Kb7
$19) 45... Kb7 46. Nd5 Bc6 {Black threatens to win material: Bc6xd5} (46... h4
$142 $19 {it becomes clear that Black will call all the shots}) 47. Ne7 $11 {
White has a mate threat} Bd7 48. Kf3 $4 {releasing the pressure on the opponent
} (48. Nd5 h4 $19) 48... h4 (48... g5 $142 $19 {and Black wins}) 49. Nxg6 $11
Kxb6 50. Nxh4 Kxc7 51. Ke4 Kc6 52. Kd4 Bh3 53. Ng6 Bg2 54. Nh4 1/2-1/2

