Bd2 dxe4 13. Nxe4 Qd8 14. Bb4 O-O 15. Ne5 f6 16. Nf3 a5 17. Ba3 Ra7 18. Nd6 Bd7
19. Bc5 Ra8 20. Nb7 Qe8 21. Qd2 a4 22. bxa4 Rxa4 23. Qc2 {Kuzmin,G (2560)
-Kurajica,B (2490) Yerevan 1971 1-0 (37)}) 9. Bg5 $146 (9. e5 O-O 10. Nc3 h6
11. b3 Bd7 12. Ba3 Re8 13. Qd2 Qa5 14. Bc5 Nf5 15. Bd3 b6 16. b4 Nxb4 17. Bxf5
gxf5 18. Bd6 Rac8 19. Re3 f4 20. Ree1 Nc2 21. Qxc2 Qxc3 22. Qe2 Rc4 23. a4 Rec8
{Blees,A (2389)-Van der Weide,K (2467) Amsterdam 2000 1/2-1/2 (49)}) (9. Bxc6+
bxc6 10. e5 O-O 11. Nc3 Qc7 12. Na4 Bb7 13. b3 Rfe8 14. Bg5 Nc8 15. Qd2 Nb6 16.
Nc5 a5 17. Bh6 a4 18. b4 Ba6 19. a3 Bb5 20. h4 Nd7 21. Nxd7 Qxd7 22. Nh2 Qe7
23. Bxg7 Kxg7 {Kalinitschew,S (2491)-Bartels,H (2170) Bad Wiessee 2000 1-0 (41)
}) 9... h6 (9... dxe4 10. Rxe4 O-O 11. Nc3 $11) 10. Bh4 (10. Bxe7 $142 $5 Kxe7
11. exd5 Nxd4 12. Nc3 Nxb5 13. Nxb5 $16) 10... O-O (10... dxe4 11. Bxe7 (11.
Rxe4 $2 g5 $19) 11... Kxe7 12. Rxe4 Nxd4 13. Nxd4 $11) 11. Nc3 (11. exd5 Qxd5
12. Nc3 Qd7 $14) 11... Qc7 (11... g5 $5 {is worth consideration} 12. exd5 Nxd4
13. Nxd4 gxh4 $15) 12. Bg3 {White threatens to win material: Bg3xc7} Qd8 13.
Rc1 (13. exd5 $5 exd5 14. Ne5 $14) 13... dxe4 $11 14. Rxe4 {Black has a
cramped position} (14. Nxe4 f5 (14... Nxd4 $143 15. Nxd4 a6 16. Ba4 $16) 15.
Nc5 f4 $11) 14... Nf5 {[%cal Rc6d4,Rd8d4,Rf5d4,Rg7d4,Gd1d4,Ge4d4,Gf3d4]
Increasing the pressure on the isolated pawn on d4} (14... f5 $142 $5 15. Re1
f4 $15) 15. Bxc6 $11 bxc6 {Black has the pair of bishops} 16. Be5 Bb7 (16... f6
17. Bg3 $11) 17. Bxg7 $14 Kxg7 18. Re1 Qc7 19. Ne4 Qb6 (19... Rad8 20. g4 Ne7
21. Rc3 $16) 20. b3 (20. g4 $5 Ne7 21. Ne5 $16) 20... Rad8 $14 21. Nc5 {
A classical outpost} Qc7 (21... Rd5 $142 $5 $14 {is an interesting alternative}
) 22. Rxe6 $1 $16 {registering a claim to victory.} Bc8 (22... fxe6 23. Nxe6+
Kf6 (23... Kf7 24. Nxc7 {Combination}) (23... Kg8 24. Nxc7 {Combination}) (
23... Kh7 24. Nxc7 {Combination}) (23... Kh8 24. Nxc7 {Combination}) 24. Nxc7 {
Combination}) 23. Re4 Nd6 24. Re1 Bf5 (24... f6 25. Qd2 $16) 25. Nh4 (25. h3
Bc8 $18) 25... Bc8 26. b4 (26. h3 Rfe8 $16) 26... Nb7 (26... Nb5 27. Rc4 $16)
27. Qb3 (27. Nf3 Nxc5 28. Rxc5 Qd6 $18) 27... Nxc5 28. dxc5 Be6 29. Qc3+ Kg8 $4
{a blunder in a bad position} (29... Kh7 $142 30. a4 a6 $16) 30. Qf6 $18 Bd5 (
30... Rd2 {is the last straw} 31. Nxg6 $1 {Deflection: e6} fxg6 32. Qxg6+ Qg7
33. Qxe6+ Qf7 34. Qxc6 Rxf2 $18) 31. Re7 Rd7 (31... Qxe7 {doesn't improve
anything} 32. Qxe7 Rde8 33. Qxa7 Re4 $18) 32. Rxd7 (32. Nxg6 Qe5 33. Qxe5 f6
34. Qf5 Rb7 35. Rxb7 Rb8 36. Ne7+ Kf7 37. Qg6+ Kf8 38. Rxb8+ Kxe7 39. Qe8#)
32... Qxd7 $14 33. Rd1 Qg4 {Black has a mate threat} 34. Rd4 {White threatens
to win material: Rd4xg4} Qe2 (34... Re8 35. h3 (35. Rxg4 $4 {mating in 1} Re1#)
35... Re1+ 36. Kh2 $11) 35. h3 $16 Qxa2 36. Nxg6 $4 {White loses the upper hand
} (36. Kh2 $142 Qb1 37. Rg4 $16) 36... fxg6 $4 {a weak move, ruining a winning
position} (36... Qb1+ 37. Rd1 Qxg6 (37... Qxd1+ $6 38. Kh2 fxg6 39. Qxg6+ Kh8
40. Qxh6+ Kg8 41. Qg6+ Kh8 42. Qh6+ Kg8 43. Qg6+ Kh8 44. Qh6+ $11) (37... fxg6
$4 38. Qxf8+ (38. Rxb1 $2 {may look interesting but causes some serious
problems} Rxf6 39. b5 cxb5 $19) 38... Kxf8 39. Rxb1 $18) 38. Qxg6+ fxg6 $19)
37. Qxg6+ Kh8 38. Qxh6+ Kg8 39. Qg6+ Kh8 40. Rh4# 1-0

